<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8975&amp;p=95052#p95052</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8975&amp;p=95052#p95052"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[NTSC borders in emulators]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8975&amp;p=95052#p95052"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">koitsu wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />Bregalad, in the <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UITwFE04wh0#t=89s" class="postlink">reference video</a> there is significantly more than 2 pixels on the right and left which are colour #0.  Did I misunderstand what you wrote?<br /></div><br />Yes, you misunderstood me (you know I'm no a native English)<br /><br />On NTSC :<br />The PPU renders MORE than 256 "pixels" each scanline, the additional "pixels" are colour palette #0 - or BG colour.<br /><br />On PAL:<br />The PPU renders only 252 "pixels", the leftmost and rightmost 2 pixels are systematically hidden, and the border area is always black, no matter the BG colour.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38">Bregalad</a> — Tue Jun 05, 2012 6:40 am</p><hr />
