<title type="html"><![CDATA[NTSC borders in emulators]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8975&amp;p=95042#p95042"><![CDATA[
NTSC NES has borders on left and right sides of the screen. The color of the borders is the current background color. For an example see <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UITwFE04wh0#t=89s" class="postlink">Mickey's Adventure in Numberland</a> (background color is yellow on the top part and black on the bottom part).<br /><br />Are there any emulators that render these borders?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=80">thefox</a> — Tue Jun 05, 2012 3:35 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
